<p><a href="#_ednref17" name="_edn17">[17]</a> Lymari Morales, “Majority in U.S. Continues to Distrust the Media, Perceive Bias,” <i>Gallup</i>, September 22, 2011, https://news.gallup.com/poll/149624/majority-continue-distrust-media-perceive-bias.aspx.</p>
<p><a href="#_ednref18" name="_edn18">[18]</a> Tim Groseclose, <i>Left Turn: How Liberal Media Bias Distorts the American Mind</i> (New York: St. Martin&#8217;s Press, 2011).</p>
<p><a href="#_ednref19" name="_edn19">[19]</a> Tim Groseclose, <i>Left Turn: How Liberal Media Bias Distorts the American Mind</i>, Chapter 10, “The Second-Order Problem of an Unbalanced Newsroom.”</p>
<p><a href="#_ednref20" name="_edn20">[20]</a> Lydia Saad, “U.S. Conservatives Outnumber Liberals by Narrowing Margin,” <i>Gallup</i>, January 2017, https://news.gallup.com/poll/201152/conservative-liberal-gap-continues-narrow-tuesday.aspx.</p>
<p><a href="#_ednref21" name="_edn21">[21]</a> Chris Cillizza, “Just 7 Percent of Journalists Are Republicans. That’s Far Fewer than Even a Decade Ago,” <i>Washington Post</i>, May 6, 2014,<i> </i>https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2014/05/06/just-7-percent-of-journalists-are-republicans-thats-far-less-than-even-a-decade-ago/?noredirect=on&amp;utm_term=.3d0109901e1e.</p>
